originalText.text: Dr Moisa-Babii is a wonderful doctor. I moved to NYC from another state mid-pregnancy and worried about the kind of care I would receive but my fears were quickly put to rest after my initial appointments with her. I find Dr. Moisa very calming and nurturing. She has never made me feel rushed and has always taken her time to ask important questions or to explain things to this first time mom. I consider myself lucky to have had her deliver my baby.

originalText.text:
Dr. Ecaterina Moisa-Babii is the worst doctor I have ever had. I took the first appointment so I could get to work (also work at a hospital so I understand the importance of being there for patients) and she arrived over 2 hours late. The receptionist kept coming in and apologizing and she attempted to call the doctor several times but she wouldn't pick up. When she finally arrived, she did not apologize or explain herself. I felt weird prodding so I just went with it. As a result, my own patients were kept waiting at work because of her negligence.

A few weeks later I ran out of medication because I was traveling and left it in the hotel. I asked her for a refill and she didn't respond to any of my calls or messages. She could simply say she needed another appointment or explain but she just continued to be negligent of her patients. I had my pharmacy contact her as well and she never responded. She is horrible and I have switched my doctor elsewhere. Stay away

originalText.text:
I have been seeing Dr. Moisa throughout my pregnancy and she has been very professional and kind, always answering all the questions and concerns of a sometimes worrisome first time mom.
She showed great bedside manners and a genuine and straightforward approach when dealing with my concerns regarding a few complications I had during my pregnancy.
